cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks in text domain to adversarial attacks and defenses. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the efficiency and limitations of countermeasures, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper discusses the security aspect of deep neural networks, it may also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, since adversarial examples are also present in image recognition, it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
